The President signed three bills into law. The first is the "Firefighter Cancer Registry Act of 2018," which creates a voluntary registry to collect data on cancer incidence among firefighters. The second is the "All Circuit Review Act," which grants permanent authority for judicial review of certain decisions related to whistleblowers by the Merit Systems Protection Board. The third is the "Supporting Grandparents Raising Grandchildren Act," which establishes an Advisory Council to support grandparents who are raising their grandchildren.